0x4301E10C.name: GET_SHAPE_TEST_RESULT_INCLUDING_MATERIAL

params.name: hit
params.description: Whether or not the shape test hit any collisions.

params.name: endCoords
params.description: The resulting coordinates where the shape test hit a collision.

params.name: surfaceNormal
params.description: The surface normal of the hit position.

params.name: materialHash
params.description: hash of the hit material or surface type, see materialFX.dat

params.name: entityHit
params.description: Any dynamic entity hit by the shape test.

0x4301E10C.description:
Returns the result of a shape test, also returning the material of any touched surface.

When used with an asynchronous shape test, this native should be looped until returning 0 or 2, after which the handle is invalidated.

Unless the return value is 2, the other return values are undefined.
0x4301E10C.resultsDescription: `0` if the handle is invalid, `1` if the shape test is still pending, or `2` if the shape test has completed, and the handle should be invalidated.
